      "content": "i see. so it's almost like a trade-off. but i've seen some people saying that if the UN's structure is designed to protect the interests of a few specific countries, then it's not really a \"global\" institution at all, but more of an exclusive club. do historians consider that a legitimate critique of its authority, or do they mostly see it as an unavoidable reality of how the world works?",
